HB 621 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Coates
Abstract: Requires decommissioning plans to include recycling of renewable energy
components or infrastructure to the extent practicable subject to the applicable
provisions of the La. Admin. Code.
Proposed law requires that decommissioning plans for renewable energy facilities include
recycling of components or infrastructure of the facility to the extent practicable in
accordance with provisions of the Dept. of Environmental Quality regulations pertaining to
Universal Wastes, Recyclable Materials, and Recycling and Waste Reduction Rules in the
La. Admin. Code.
Redesignates the headings of present law provisions providing for batteries, wind energy,
and solar power generation facilities.
Effective Jan. 1, 2027.
(Adds R.S. 30:1121)
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Natural Resources and
Environment to the original bill:
1. Specify the regulations of the Department of Environmental Quality pertaining
to Universal Wastes and Recyclable Materials in the Louisiana Administrative
Code to which the decommissioning plans must comply.
2. Remove the requirement for costs of decommissioning, including recycling of
components or infrastructure, to be borne by the renewable energy facility
owner.
3. Add an effective date.
